## Context
Reviewer 2 (general + linear) + Reviewer 1 other comments: replace abstract /
declarative passages with concrete actors, sites, instruments, dates, and
consequences.

This is now a **tracking ticket**. The passage-level R2 list below is split into
PR-sized children, one manuscript region each. The tracker stays open until every
child is closed, then closes only after an integration re-read of the combined
diff against the R2 list.

## Children (split 2026-07-08)
- **0189** — Article 4.3 → Bali: incremental-cost framework and the shift to a
  broader category (§2.1; R2p, R2w; welfare-transfers p8).
- **0190** — CDM functioning and the migration of carbon accounting (§2.2;
  post-2012 demand; carbon vs financial accounting).
- **0191** — the $100bn, the Baku gap, the scale of the number (§2.3/§3; $100bn
  provenance + Copenhagen; scale vs ~$1.01T US defense; Baku 1.3T/0.3T gap;
  Southern "combien je vaux" reading; p16 UN Advisory Group). *Cluster informally
  called "141B"; a parallel session is editing these passages.*
- **0192** — competing measurement regimes: Rio markers, UNFCCC reporting, OECD
  expert groups; connect the Desrosières quote (p7) to the empirical case (§2.3).
- **0193** — the 2007/Stern "new economic object" claim (R2y) and the
  performativity passage (R2x, R2z, R2ad); consistent with the R2.21 narrowing in
  0136.
- **0194** — Türkiye worked case ↔ four-controversies mapping (§3.1; R2.g2/R2.34).

## Routed to existing siblings (not duplicated here)
- Development-economics section + naming the OECD development economists → **0135**.
- Models-vs-accounting-infrastructure (IAMs vs DAC, p3) + "longer trajectory of
  climate economics" + finance-development framing → **0139**.
- Why borrowing the aid reporting system is problematic → substantively covered by
